text.section:
Under the circumstances stated in subsection (a) of this section, the driver of an emergency vehicle may:
Park or stand without regard to the other provisions of this title;
Pass a red or stop signal, a stop sign, or a yield sign, but only after slowing down as necessary for safety;
Exceed any maximum speed limit, but only so long as the driver does not endanger life or property; and
Disregard any traffic control device or regulation governing direction of movement or turning in a specified direction.
